At the end of the trade, the Prague stock exchange bascula in the negative
After the fall of Tuesday morning, the Prague Stock Exchange rectified its losses.
Transactions with the shares ČEZ reached almost half of the usual daily exchanges.
On Tuesday, from the beginning of the trade, the Prague Stock Exchange resumed with its fall of the day before, when it lost almost six percent.
This time, the decline is due to the fall in shares on Wall Street.
The reaction of the market to the result of the vote of the American House of Representatives, which refused to adopt the plan for the stabilization of the US financial sector, is also noticeable in our home.
Action crash in Asia
The Asian fellowships experienced a dramatic fall on Tuesday, even if the clues were able, during the day, to erase some of the losses.
The Hang Seng Index of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange lost four percent during trade, but later it erased part of the losses and reduced the decline to about 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index following the Chinese stock movement of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange lost 3.8 percent, with markets closed in Shanghai.
The Sydney stock market lost more than five per cent, but eventually the losses were reduced to 4.3 per cent.
According to its index, the Taiwan Stock Exchange lost 3.6 percent.
"The hesitation about the rescue action in the US will affect the financial markets around the world," observes Joseph Yam, head of Hong Kong's monetary office.
Although Hong Kong is part of China, it establishes its own monetary policy, i.e. independently of the Chinese central bank.
Interest rates in Hong Kong have the same level as in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, US legislators should quickly resume negotiations and adopt the financial system's support proposal.
Otherwise, other countries would be at risk for impact.
The bloodbath of American actions
On Monday, the US House of Representatives rejected the financial system support project, to which it should have spent up to $700 billion (nearly 12 billion Kč).
Legislators thus renegotiate the call for support for President Bush's project.
According to Bush, the project should address the main causes of the financial crisis and help stabilize the entire economy.
The American actions experienced, on Monday, a bloodbath and the main indices of actions experienced the greatest fall in the last 20 years.
The Dow Jones index lost nearly seven percent, having experienced a fall of such a magnitude for the last time in 1987.
The index was already lost during the vote, but when it appeared that the proposal was not adopted, it was in free fall.
Congress ceda: US government can inject $700 billion into banks
The leaders of the U.S. Congress and the government of President George W. Bush agreed on a broader form of the financial aid agreement to the U.S. financial system.
It will be put to the vote early next week.
U.S. legislators made a decisive turn in the talks on the adoption of a rescue plan in the form of financial assistance of $700 billion (about 12 trillion crowns) granted to the U.S. financial system.
Success is not safe at all.
Indeed, before the final version of the law can be published and put to the vote, Congressmen must complete a number of details of the agreement.
The financial system support plan will be discussed in the House of Representatives on Monday.
Says Sunday to Reuters Barney Frank, president of the Chamber's Banking and Financial Regulatory Committee.
According to sources, on Wednesday at the earliest, the plan should a priori be put to the vote in the Senate.
According to economists, the announcement that the rescue plan will be adopted should be a major psychological factor in reinvigorating financial markets.
Given the complexity of the mechanisms through which market aid can be effective, it will follow a "disillusion".
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We have made great progress.
We have settled our divergent views on the form that the package of measures for market stabilization should have," the Democrat Nancy Pelosi entrusted to the Bloomberg Agency.
According to her, the final vote could be taken on Sunday.
On the night of Saturday to Sunday, representatives of the legislators met with US finance minister Henry Paulson, in order to give the bottom of the government a final form.
The latter should buy back from financial companies the unsaleable real estate assets that cause financial enterprises to suffer considerable losses and threaten the stability of the system as a whole.
"We are about to agree on a plan that will work and that must also be effective on the market.
