The pragmatic public transport (MHD) will introduce, on Wednesday, the chip in their ticketing system
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be inscribed in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Agency for Transport) as the date on which the first passengers, instead of having a ticket in paper, will get an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible for about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it registered on their smart card at the Dopravní podnik (Transport Agency) information points and offices located at the Muzeum, Městek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letñany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka metro stations.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons via internet on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can definitively forget the counters in the subway stations, where they had until now to trample impatience in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon online and will be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is a window available to passengers with trained staff, which will help interested people with the internet purchase and, in addition, will record the coupon they bought on their card," says the spokesman for the Martin Opartrný project.
Next to the libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in vending machines installed in the lobby of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, reminding the machines to compose tickets and the passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budějoviká, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
An automaton will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow, are easy to use.
Simply insert the Opencard chip card and the coupon previously purchased will register itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also in the surroundings of the city.
For example, in the peri-urban trains and bus lines 300 to 499, which are mainly used by the inhabitants of the communes of the Central Bohemia to access the capital.
