An emotional campaign will attack the drivers
The most expensive road safety action in Czech history.
A way to characterize the emotional media campaign that the Ministry of Transport intends to launch on Wednesday.
Minister Aleš Åebíček's office believes that it will discourage drivers from dangerous driving behaviour.
This campaign, costing 150 million, will appear on television, radio, cinema, the Internet, but also on leaflets.
It should discourage drivers from driving fast and alcohol in the steering wheel.
