Above all, it wants to reach the consciousness of young drivers, bikers, pedestrians, not to mention professional drivers.
What will appear in the spots?
Especially personal stories that will attack emotions.
It also bears witness to the "sanglant" slogan of the whole campaign:
You don't think - you pay!
The phrase "You don't think" is inscribed in capital letters on the registration plate.
Then, in a bloodthirsty, there's the phrase "You'll pay."
Which has to symbolize that life can be paid for a moment of carelessness.
The spots will "haunt" the spectators until 2010.
The ministry has been inspired by similar campaigns in Anglo-Saxon countries, where images can be seen commonly with drastic images of accident victims.
