Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the car illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the bus company Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the bus.
"If the law is to be strictly and formally respected, the activity of a steward is contrary to the Law on Road Traffic," said the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus path.
The girl was unfortunately sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she has two other seats at her disposal.
However, the bus can have an accident or even suddenly brake, also at the time when the steward serves coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is under its technical specification equipped with standing or not seats.
If this equipment for standing seats is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
Long distance buses Student Agency do not have standing seats; this was confirmed at Aktuálně.cz by the director of the company Radim Jančura.
"It's a matter we've been dealing with with with the ministry, and at first, it bans any movement of passengers.
Then they cancelled it and we got that passengers can go to the bathroom during the journey provided they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no single legal interpretation of the role of steward - no legal requirement deals with this role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement also prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport knows only the term "vehicle receiver"; it does not define its rights and duties," adds the spokesman Hanzelka more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorný, director of the Road Traffic Department, believes, on the contrary, that the law deals with the problem sufficiently.
"It all depends on whether the bus has in its approval permission to offer standing seats.
Everything resides in it," he says.
The buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, long distance with standing places and a higher authorized speed and long distance buses without standing places with the highest permitted maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As in the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hořín, an expert in BESIP (road traffic safety) in safety in transport, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"When there is regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Also there, it is not safe when turbulence occurs and the hostesse of the air can hit its head."
"But in the event that the coach would have stopped abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
The same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal requirements," he said and also felt that from the point of view of the law, the problem was not solved.
Jančura is ready to delete these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer the services of stewards.
He hires two hundred of them.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their job a risky job.
"Nevertheless, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky trade, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper on board.
This would also reduce the cost," he says.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexeï Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses, we've been opposing them since the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end up in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, at Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has arrived
A young hostess from the Plzeń region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably took off the emergency stop tape without using a flashing device and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he frowned on his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but for the financial compensation, it will also rely on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in view
An amendment to the law, which has been being prepared for more than a year by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide details on the travel of stewards on board the coach.
"But it did not come to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not interested too much in buses, but rather in the point system, at the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile phone by the steering wheel," says expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not regard the activity of stewards as a thing that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," said the spokesman Hanzelka, stating that the control of the safety of buses is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
