Recidivists of alcohol in the steering wheel will have to install the 'alcolock' system
The Minister of the Interior wants the driver who has had more than three administrative penalties for alcohol, to have to install in his vehicle a system that prevents the vehicle from starting in a state of drunkenness, or if it does not blow.
The initiative has already been announced last June and is now reflected in the report of the Minister of State in which this initiative is considered a pilot project that will last one year.
Its purpose is to reintegrate the driver by offering him courses in road rehabilitation.
The Minister of State for Road Safety, as well as the Directorate-General for Road Safety and the Technological Institute for Automotive Safety Foundation, will participate in this initiative.
According to the statistics, between 30% and 75% of the drivers arrested for driving more than once in a state of drunkenness, the car resumes.
Alcoholock would avoid this because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the alcohol level in the breath and prevents the vehicle from starting if the driver does not blow ahead; or when the alcohol level of the driver is higher than that allowed.
Its cost is more than 1000 euros and is at the driver's expense.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with this device reduced up to 65% of the infringements during the first year of installation.
And in Spain it is estimated that this could save the lives of 115 people every year.
This measure is based only on administrative sanctions for two reasons: dealing with these behaviours before they turn into criminal offences.
And to facilitate its implementation, since legal reform can be done by ordinary means but, however, reform by criminal means requires reform of the organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial form, although some industrial and functional vehicles already have one on an experimental basis.
Precisely tomorrow, the Congress of Deputies will vote for an initiative of the Spanish Socialist Party that proposes to install in the school buses this system as it was done in France.
