"The vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment must be broken, and the opportunities provided by democracy must be given to Roma children, so that they can participate as citizens of full right in the future of Europe" - Járóka demanded.
On behalf of the European Year for Equal Opportunities for All, the objective of the Summit for Equal Opportunities in Europe, organised every year since the Berlin Summit last year, is to provide a single platform to support measures taken to promote equal opportunities and to combat discrimination, which are targeted at European and Member State levels.
